%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# URP Global Asset (UniversalRenderPipelineAsset) — STUB
#
# Placeholder for the URP pipeline asset. Author in-editor via:
#   Assets > Create > Rendering > URP > Universal Render Pipeline Asset
#
# Once created, drag it into Project Settings > Graphics > Scriptable Render
# Pipeline Settings AND into each Quality tier under Project Settings >
# Quality. The asset should reference the URPRenderer.asset created in
# parallel.
#
# Recommended values per tech-spec 06-rendering.md:
#   - Color Grading Mode: LDR (mobile cost on HDR is prohibitive)
#   - LUT Size: 32 (good quality vs memory tradeoff on mobile)
#   - Volume Update: Via Scripting (we drive volume in code from
#     Brave.Systems on biome transitions; default 'Every Frame' triggers
#     allocations).
#   - Anti-aliasing (post): None (rely on MSAA from renderer)
#   - Terrain Holes: Off
#   - HDR: Off
#   - MSAA: 2x
#   - Render Scale: 1.0
#   - Main Light: Per-Pixel
#   - Cast Shadows: Soft Shadows OFF; shadow distance 25 m for top-down cam
#   - Additional Lights: Per-Pixel, max 4
#   - Reflection Probes: Box Projection OFF
#
# Cross-reference: tech-spec 06-rendering.md (authoritative for URP knobs).
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 0}
  m_Name: URPGlobal
  m_EditorClassIdentifier:
  # NOTE: real fields populated by Unity in-editor. Delete + recreate from
  # the Editor menu on first project open.
